article.headline: UNLV 70, TCU 58
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Wink Adams scored 25 points, including 15 off 3-pointers, as UNLV beat TCU 70-58 on Wednesday night. Adams shot 8-of-17 from the field, including 5-of-10 from 3-point range. He hit all four of his free throws and also had five assists. Joe Darger added 12 points for the Runnin' Rebels, who won their fourth straight. Brent Hackett scored 19 points for TCU and Kevin Langford added 17. TCU got the opening bucket, but never led again. The score was tied five times, all in the first half. UNLV (16-4, 5-1 Mountain West) led 35-29 at the half and shot 48 percent from the field. TCU (11-8, 3-3) shot 38 percent from the field.
